am, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Little Wenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Mildenhall, Suffolk, England":"Mildenhall, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hethe","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Laurent, Normand, Philippe.","German: habitational name from Methau in Saxony.","Germanized form of Sorbian <b>Mět</b> or <b>Měto</b> (see   Mieth  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Mieth","meanings":["Germanized form of Sorbian <b>Mět</b>: either from a short form of the Old Sorbian personal name <i>Mětisław</i>, composed of the Old Slavic elements <i>met</i> ‘to throw’ (from <i>metati</i>) + <i>slav</i> ‘glory’ or ‘famous’ (from <i>slava</i> ‘glory’), or from a pet form of <i>Mertyn</i>, a Lower Sorbian form of   Martin  .","German: nickname from Middle High German <i>miet</i> ‘reward’."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Hethe was born in 1360, in Little Saxham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Hethe, was 25 and his mother, Amy de Risby, was 26. He married Margery Durward about 1380. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 21 August 1397, in his hometown, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1360–21 August 1397":"1360–21. august 1397","1360–1397":"1360–1397","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1378–Male":"1378–Surnud","1380–1428":"1380–1428","–1383":"–1383","–1415":"–1415","1360–1410":"1360–1410","1383–1439":"1383–1439","1335–1392":"1335–1392","1335–Female":"1335–Surnud","about 1380":"umbes 1380","1440":"1440","1383":"1383","1360":"1360","21 May 1383":"21. mai 1383","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1415":"1415","1335":"1335","1378":"1378","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","21 August 1397":"21. august 1397","about 1353":"umbes 1353","1439":"1439","1428":"1428","Little Saxham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Little Saxham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Little Saxham, Suffolk, England":"Little Saxham, Suffolk, England","Little Wenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Little Wenham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mildenhall, Suffolk, England":"Mildenhall, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1360–21 August 1397":"1360–21. elokuuta 1397","1360–1397":"1360–1397","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1378–Male":"1378–Kuollut","1380–1428":"1380–1428","–1383":"–1383","–1415":"–1415","1360–1410":"1360–1410","1383–1439":"1383–1439","1335–1392":"1335–1392","1335–Female":"1335–Kuollut","about 1380":"noin 1380","1440":"1440","1383":"1383","1360":"1360","21 May 1383":"21. toukokuuta 1383","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1415":"1415","1335":"1335","1378":"1378","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","21 August 1397":"21. elokuuta 1397","about 1353":"noin 1353","1439":"1439","1428":"1428","Little Saxham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Little Saxham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Little Saxham, Suffolk, England":"Little Saxham, Suffolk, England","Little Wenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Little Wenham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningas